(fifthQuint)A Study of Daily Dosing With Levalbuterol, Racemic Albuterol, and Placebo in Pediatric Subjects With Asthma.

 This was a multicenter, randomized, double-blind, placebo- and active-controlled, Phase II, parallel-group study up to four weeks in duration.

 Seven days of QID (four times a day) single-blind, placebo administration (via metered dose inhaler (MDI)) was followed by 21 days of QID double-blind treatment.

 During the single-blind period, rescue medication consisted of racemic albuterol MDI (90 mcg per actuation) for all subjects.

 During the double-blind period, rescue medication consisted of double-blind levalbuterol MDI (45 mcg per actuation) for all subjects in the levalbuterol treatment groups or double-blind racemic albuterol MDI (90 mcg per actuation) for all subjects in the racemic albuterol and placebo treatment groups.

The study consisted of two periods, an optional follow-up visit, and a final telephone evaluation.

