Multicenter, randomized, double-blind, placebo- and active-controlled, Phase II, parallel-group study of up to four weeks in duration.

 The study consisted of a screening visit followed by a one-week single blind placebo period.

 At next visit, each subject was randomized to one of four treatment groups: 90 mcg levalbuterol, 180 mcg levalbuterol, 180 mcg racemic albuterol, or placebo.

 All study medication was administered as 2 actuations 4 times a day for 21 days.

